main event: Aircrews from England AFB, LA observed an unidentified flying object on 30 September 1966.
interesting points: The object was shaped much like a shallow cereal bowl turned upside down., The color of the object appeared to be grayish white to blue with a translucent appearance., Observers estimated the diameter of the object to be between 20 to 30 feet., The object made a left turn and was noted to not bank like a fixed wing aircraft., The observation lasted approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
sighted object: a dome-shaped object resembling a shallow cereal bowl
